00:22:05,864 --> 00:22:07,698
In Little Whinging?

233
00:22:07,699 --> 00:22:10,201
That's quite clever.

234
00:22:10,202 --> 00:22:13,621
Muggles can't see Dementors,
can they, boy?

235
00:22:13,622 --> 00:22:15,915
- Highly convenient.
- I'm not lying.

236
00:22:15,916 --> 00:22:18,667
- There were two of them, if I hadn't...
- Enough.

237
00:22:18,668 --> 00:22:23,047
I'm sorry to interrupt what I'm sure
would be a very well-rehearsed story...

238
00:22:23,048 --> 00:22:27,718
but since you can produce
no witnesses of the event...

239
00:22:27,719 --> 00:22:32,719
Pardon me, minister,
but as it happens, we can.

240
00:22:35,644 --> 00:22:40,644
Please describe the attack.

241
00:22:41,525 --> 00:22:43,901
What did they look like?

242
00:22:43,902 --> 00:22:48,902
Well, one of them was very large
and the other rather skinny.

243
00:22:50,408 --> 00:22:53,410
Not the boys. The Dementors.

244
00:22:53,411 --> 00:22:58,249
Oh, right, right. Well, big.

245
00:22:58,250 --> 00:23:03,250
Cloaked. Then everything went cold...

246
00:23:03,505 --> 00:23:07,091
as though all the happiness
had gone from the world.

247
00:23:07,092 --> 00:23:12,092
Now, look here. Dementors don't just
wander into a Muggle suburb...

248
00:23:12,347 --> 00:23:16,141
and happen across a wizard.
The odds are astronomical.

249
00:23:16,142 --> 00:23:18,060
I don't think anyone would believe...

250
00:23:18,061 --> 00:23:23,061
the Dementors were there
by coincidence, minister.

251
00:23:23,608 --> 00:23:26,652
I'm sure I must have misunderstood you,
professor.

252
00:23:26,653 --> 00:23:31,653
Dementors are, after all, under
the control of the Ministry of Magic.

253
00:23:32,325 --> 00:23:36,704
And it's so silly of me, but it sounded
for a moment as though...

254
00:23:36,705 --> 00:23:40,875
you were suggesting that the Ministry
had ordered the attack on this boy.

255
00:23:40,876 --> 00:23:43,836
That would be disturbing indeed,
Madam Undersecretary...

256
00:23:43,837 --> 00:23:48,173
which is why I'm sure the Ministry
will be mounting a full-scale inquiw...

257
00:23:48,174 --> 00:23:51,719
into why the two Dementors
were so very far from Azkaban...

258
00:23:51,720 --> 00:23:55,973
and why they mounted an attack
without authorization.

259
00:23:55,974 --> 00:23:58,517
Of course, there is someone...

260
00:23:58,518 --> 00:24:03,518
who might be behind the attack.

261
00:24:04,149 --> 00:24:08,944
Cornelius, I implore you to see reason.

262
00:24:08,945 --> 00:24:13,657
The evidence that the Dark Lord
has returned is incontrovertible.

263
00:24:13,658 --> 00:24:18,658
He is not back.

264
00:24:22,334 --> 00:24:25,127
In the matter of Harry Potter...

265
00:24:25,128 --> 00:24:27,796
the law clearly states...

266
00:24:27,797 --> 00:24:32,343
that magic may be used before
Muggles in life-threatening situations.

267
00:24:32,344 --> 00:24:35,429
Laws can be changed if necessary,
Dumbledore.

268
00:24:35,430 --> 00:24:38,766
Clearly. Has it become practice
to hold a full Criminal trial...

269
00:24:38,767 --> 00:24:43,767
to deal with a simple matter
of underage magic?

270
00:24:50,028 --> 00:24:55,028
Those in favor of conviction?

271
00:25:02,415 --> 00:25:07,415
Those in favor
of clearing the accused of all Charges?

272
00:25:21,476 --> 00:25:26,476
Cleared of all Charges.

273
00:25:26,773 --> 00:25:31,773
Professor.

274
00:25:41,454 --> 00:25:44,707
Padfoot. Are you barking mad?

275
00:25:44,708 --> 00:25:49,708
You'll blow the entire operation.

276
00:25:55,427 --> 00:25:58,262
Sirius, what are you doing here?
If somebody sees you...

277
00:25:58,263 --> 00:26:02,683
I had to see you off, didn't I?

278
00:26:02,684 --> 00:26:05,394
What's life without a little risk?

279
00:26:05,395 --> 00:26:07,896
I don't wanna see you
get chucked back in Azkaban.

280
00:26:07,897 --> 00:26:09,773
Don't worry about me.

281
00:26:09,774 --> 00:26:14,774
Anyway, I wanted you to have this.

282
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:23,746
Original Order of the Phoenix.

283
00:26:23,747 --> 00:26:25,622
Marlene McKinnon.

284
00:26:25,623 --> 00:26:28,584
She was killed
two weeks after this was taken.

285
00:26:28,585 --> 00:26:32,171
Voldemort wiped out her entire family.

286
00:26:32,172 --> 00:26:34,131
Frank and Alice Longbottom.

287
00:26:34,132 --> 00:26:35,799
Neville's parents.

288
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:40,800
They suffered a fate Worse than death,
you ask me.

289
00:26:41,431 --> 00:26:44,725
It's been 14 years.

290
00:26:44,726 --> 00:26:49,726
And still a day doesn't go by
I don't miss your dad.

291
00:26:53,610 --> 00:26:58,610
Do you really think
there's going to be a war, Sirius?

292
00:26:58,948 --> 00:27:03,948
It feels like it did before.

293
00:27:06,206 --> 00:27:08,499
You keep it.

294
00:27:08,500 --> 00:27:13,500
Anyway, I suppose
you're the young ones now.

295
00:27:15,090 --> 00:27:17,091
I'll see you at the train.

296
00:27:17,092 --> 00:27:20,010
Bye-bye, darling.

297
00:27:20,011 --> 00:27:22,262
I love you.

298
00:27:22,263 --> 00:27:24,515
Hold my hand, lovey.

299
00:27:24,516 --> 00:27:26,975
There they are.
They're in the far carriage.

300
00:27:26,976 --> 00:27:27,476
Bye.

301
00:28:10,436 --> 00:28:13,564
I'm Surprised the Ministry's
still letting you walk around free.

302
00:28:13,565 --> 00:28:15,232
Better enjoy it while you can.

303
00:28:15,233 --> 00:28:20,233
I expect there's a cell in Azkaban
with your name on it.

304
00:28:21,114 --> 00:28:26,114
- What'd I tell you? Complete nutter.
- Just stay away from me!

305
00:28:26,286 --> 00:28:28,954
It's only Malfoy.

306
00:28:28,955 --> 00:28:33,955
What'd you expect?

307
00:28:50,768 --> 00:28:52,102
Hi, guys.

308
00:28:52,103 --> 00:28:57,103
- Hey, Nevme.
- Hey there, Neville.

309
00:29:06,826 --> 00:29:10,537
What is it?

310
00:29:10,538 --> 00:29:14,625
- What's what?
- That. Pulling the carriage.

311
00:29:14,626 --> 00:29:17,586
Nothing's pulling the carriage, Harry.

312
00:29:17,587 --> 00:29:22,587
It's pulling itself, like always.

313
00:29:33,436 --> 00:29:38,232
You're not going mad.

314
00:29:38,233 --> 00:29:41,735
I can see them too.

315
00:29:41,736 --> 00:29:46,736
You're just as sane as I am.

316
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:53,997
Everyone, this is Loony Love...

317
00:29:53,998 --> 00:29:58,998
Luna Lovegood.

318
00:29:59,837 --> 00:30:02,714
What an interesting necklace.

319
00:30:02,715 --> 00:30:06,260
It's a charm, actually.

320
00:30:06,261 --> 00:30:11,261
Keeps away the Nargles.

321
00:30:11,641 --> 00:30:13,809
Hungry-

322
00:30:13,810 --> 00:30:16,770
I hope there's pudding.

323
00:30:16,771 --> 00:30:21,771
- What's a Nargle?
- No idea.

324
00:30:33,079 --> 00:30:35,998
Good evening, children.

325
00:30:35,999 --> 00:30:38,875
Now, we have two changes
in staffing this year.

326
00:30:38,876 --> 00:30:42,087
We're pleased to welcome back
Professor Grubbly-Plank...

327
00:30:42,088 --> 00:30:44,840
who'll be taking
Care of Magical Creatures...

328
00:30:44,841 --> 00:30:49,136
while Professor Hagrid
is on temporary leave.

329
00:30:49,137 --> 00:30:53,307
We also wish to welcome our new
Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher...

330
00:30:53,308 --> 00:30:56,768
Professor Dolores Umbridge.

331
00:30:56,769 --> 00:31:01,315
And I'm sure you'll all join me
in wishing the professor good luck.

332
00:31:01,316 --> 00:31:06,316
Now, as usual, our caretaker, Mr. Filch,
has asked me to remind you...

333
00:31:17,415 --> 00:31:20,292
She was at my hearing.
She works for Fudge.

334
00:31:20,293 --> 00:31:25,293
Thank you, headmaster,
for those kind words of welcome.

335
00:31:27,383 --> 00:31:31,219
And how lovely to see all your bright...

336
00:31:31,220 --> 00:31:34,431
happy faces smiling up at me.

337
00:31:34,432 --> 00:31:39,432
I'm sure we're all going
to be very good friends.

338
00:31:39,771 --> 00:31:44,771
- That's likely.
- That's likely.

339
00:31:44,859 --> 00:31:47,986
The Ministry of Magic
has always considered...

340
00:31:47,987 --> 00:31:52,987
the education of young witches
and wizards to be of vital importance.

341
00:31:53,951 --> 00:31:56,411
Although each headmaster...

342
00:31:56,412 --> 00:32:01,412
has brought something new
to this historic school...

343
00:32:02,794 --> 00:32:07,794
progress for the sake of progress
must be discouraged.

344
00:32:09,675 --> 00:32:13,678
Let us preserve
what must be preserved...

345
00:32:13,679 --> 00:32:17,349
perfect what can be perfected...

346
00:32:17,350 --> 00:32:22,350
and prune practices
that ought to be prohibited.

347
00:32:31,030 --> 00:32:35,325
Thank you, Professor Umbridge.
That really was most illuminating.

348
00:32:35,326 --> 00:32:40,326
- Illuminating? What a load of waffle.
- What's it mean?

349
00:32:40,415 --> 00:32:42,749
Magic is forbidden in the corridors...

350
00:32:42,750 --> 00:32:47,750
It means the Ministry's
interfering at Hogwarts.

351
00:33:06,107 --> 00:33:08,150
Dean, Seamus.

352
00:33:08,151 --> 00:33:10,652
- Good holiday?
- All right.

353
00:33:10,653 --> 00:33:14,197
Better than Seamus', anyway.

354
00:33:14,198 --> 00:33:16,700
Me mum didn't want me
to come back this year.

355
00:33:16,701 --> 00:33:20,412
- Why not?
- Let me see. Because of you.

356
00:33:20,413 --> 00:33:23,957
The <i>Daily</i> Prophet's been saying a lot
of things about you and Dumbledore.

357
00:33:23,958 --> 00:33:25,459
What, your mum believes them?

358
00:33:25,460 --> 00:33:27,544
Nobody was there
the night Cedric died.

359
00:33:27,545 --> 00:33:30,797
I guess you should read the Prophet,
then, like your stupid mother.

360
00:33:30,798 --> 00:33:34,468
Don't talk about my mother. - I'll
have a go at anyone Calling me a liar.

361
00:33:34,469 --> 00:33:37,137
- What's going on?
- He's mad, is what's going on.

362
00:33:37,138 --> 00:33:40,390
Do you believe the rubbish he's
come out with about You-Know-Who?

363
00:33:40,391 --> 00:33:43,059
Yeah. I do.

364
00:33:43,060 --> 00:33:48,060
Has anyone else
got a problem with Harry?

365
00:33:54,447 --> 00:33:57,032
- You all right?
- Fine.

366
00:33:57,033 --> 00:34:00,410
Seamus was bang out of order, mate.

367
00:34:00,411 --> 00:34:05,411
- But he'll come through, you'll see.
- I said, I'm fine, Ron.

368
00:34:07,835 --> 00:34:12,835
Right. I'll just leave you
to your thoughts, then.

369
00:34:40,660 --> 00:34:41,160
<i>Harry.</i>

370
00:34:57,134 --> 00:35:00,220
Bring it over here. Over here.

371
00:35:00,221 --> 00:35:05,221
Oh, go on, Seamus. Go on, get it.

372
00:35:18,739 --> 00:35:22,158
Good morning, children.

373
00:35:22,159 --> 00:35:27,159
Ordinary Wizarding Level examinations.

374
00:35:27,498 --> 00:35:30,250
O-W-Ls.

375
00:35:30,251 --> 00:35:35,005
More commonly known as OWLs.

376
00:35:35,006 --> 00:35:38,466
Study hard and you will be rewarded.

377
00:35:38,467 --> 00:35:43,467
Fail to do so,
and the consequences may be severe.

378
00:35:49,312 --> 00:35:54,312
Your previous instruction in this subject
has been disturbingly uneven.

379
00:35:54,525 --> 00:35:56,860
But you'll be pleased to know,
from now on...

380
00:35:56,861 --> 00:36:00,530
you will be following a carefully
structured, Ministry-approved...

381
00:36:00,531 --> 00:36:04,534
course of defensive magic. Yes?

382
00:36:04,535 --> 00:36:07,329
There's nothing in here
about using defensive spells?

383
00:36:07,330 --> 00:36:09,039
Using spells?

384
00:36:09,040 --> 00:36:14,040
Well, I can't imagine why you would
need to use spells in my classroom.

385
00:36:14,211 --> 00:36:15,962
We're not gonna use magic?

386
00:36:15,963 --> 00:36:20,963
You'll be learning about defensive spells
in a Secure, risk-free way.

387
00:36:21,135 --> 00:36:24,054
What use is that?
If we're attacked, it won't be risk-free.

388
00:36:24,055 --> 00:36:29,055
Students will raise their hands
when they speak in my class.

389
00:36:30,645 --> 00:36:33,229
It is the view of the Ministry...

390
00:36:33,230 --> 00:36:36,149
that a theoretical knowledge
will be sufficient...

391
00:36:36,150 --> 00:36:38,276
to get you through
your examinations...

392
00:36:38,277 --> 00:36:40,904
which, after all,
is what school is all about.

393
00:36:40,905 --> 00:36:43,865
And how's theory supposed
to prepare us for what's out there?

394
00:36:43,866 --> 00:36:46,076
There is nothing out there, dear.

395
00:36:46,077 --> 00:36:49,245
Who do you imagine
wants to attack children like yourself?

396
00:36:49,246 --> 00:36:54,246
Oh, I don't know.
Maybe Lord Voldemort.

397
00:37:03,219 --> 00:37:08,219
Now, let me make this quite plain.

398
00:37:08,265 --> 00:37:09,891
You have been told...

399
00:37:09,892 --> 00:37:14,892
that a certain dark Wizard
is at large once again.

400
00:37:15,439 --> 00:37:20,439
- This is a lie.
- It's not a lie. I saw him. I fought him.

401
00:37:20,736 --> 00:37:22,529
Detention, Mr. Potter.

402
00:37:22,530 --> 00:37:24,864
Cedric Diggory dropped dead
of his own accord?

403
00:37:24,865 --> 00:37:27,450
Cedric Diggory's death
was a tragic accident.

404
00:37:27,451 --> 00:37:29,786
It was murder. Voldemort killed him.

405
00:37:29,787 --> 00:37:31,955
Enough!

406
00:37:31,956 --> 00:37:33,790
Enough.

407
00:37:33,791 --> 00:37:38,791
See me later, Mr. Potter. My office.

408
00:38:02,862 --> 00:38:03,406
Come in.

409
00:38:09,326 --> 00:38:11,870
Good evening, Mr. Potter.

410
00:38:11,871 --> 00:38:12,371
Sit.

411
00:38:20,838 --> 00:38:24,924
You're going to be doing some lines
for me today, Mr. Potter.

412
00:38:24,925 --> 00:38:27,010
No, not with your quill.

413
00:38:27,011 --> 00:38:32,011
Going to be using
a rather special one of mine.

414
00:38:35,352 --> 00:38:37,729
Now...

415
00:38:37,730 --> 00:38:42,730
I want you to write,
"I must not tell lies."

416
00:38:45,696 --> 00:38:48,031
How many times?

417
00:38:48,032 --> 00:38:53,032
Well, let's say for as long as it takes
for the message to sink in.

418
00:38:54,705 --> 00:38:56,539
You haven't given me any ink.

419
00:38:56,540 --> 00:39:01,540
Oh, you won't need any ink.

420
00:39:49,260 --> 00:39:49,760
Yes?

421
00:39:58,102 --> 00:40:02,397
- Nothing.
- That's right.

422
00:40:02,398 --> 00:40:06,526
Because you know, deep down...

423
00:40:06,527 --> 00:40:09,779
you deserve to be punished.

424
00:40:09,780 --> 00:40:14,780
Don't you, Mr. Potter?

425
00:40:16,161 --> 00:40:16,661
Go on.

426
00:40:26,797 --> 00:40:29,257
- Skiving Snackboxes.
- Sweets that make you ill.

427
00:40:29,258 --> 00:40:31,050
Get out of class whenever you like.

428
00:40:31,051 --> 00:40:35,805
Obtain hours of pleasure
from unprofitable boredom.

429
00:40:35,806 --> 00:40:37,307
Care for another?

430
00:40:37,308 --> 00:40:40,018
- I'm not asking you to write all of it.
- Please.

431
00:40:40,019 --> 00:40:43,479
I've been busy studying
for these stupid OWL exams.

432
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:45,440
I'll do the introduction. That's all.

433
00:40:45,441 --> 00:40:49,360
Hermione, you're honestly the most
wonderful person I've ever met.

434
00:40:49,361 --> 00:40:54,361
- And if I'm ever rude to you again...
- I'll know you've gone back to normal.

435
00:40:58,662 --> 00:41:01,289
What's wrong with your hand?

436
00:41:01,290 --> 00:41:04,000
Nothing.

437
00:41:04,001 --> 00:41:08,421
The other hand.

438
00:41:08,422 --> 00:41:10,423
- You've got to tell Dumbledore.
- No.

439
00:41:10,424 --> 00:41:12,800
Dumbledore's got enough
on his mind right now.

440
00:41:12,801 --> 00:41:15,094
I don't want to give
Umbridge the satisfaction.

441
00:41:15,095 --> 00:41:17,680
Bloody hell, Harry.
The woman's torturing you.

442
00:41:17,681 --> 00:41:22,681
- If the parents knew about this...
- I haven't got any of those, have I, Ron?

443
00:41:24,438 --> 00:41:27,065
Harry, you've got to report this.

444
00:41:27,066 --> 00:41:30,777
- It's perfectly simple. You're being...
- No, it's not.

445
00:41:30,778 --> 00:41:34,656
Hermione, whatever this is,
it's not simple.

446
00:41:34,657 --> 00:41:39,285
You don't understand.

447
00:41:39,286 --> 00:41:44,286
Then help us to.

448
00:41:55,928 --> 00:41:58,346
<i>Dear Padfoot.</i> ..

449
00:41:58,347 --> 00:42:00,223
<i>I hope you're all right.</i>

450
00:42:00,224 --> 00:42:05,224
<i>It's starting to get colder here.
Winter is definitely on the way.</i>

451
00:42:07,481 --> 00:42:12,481
<i>In spite of being back at Hogwarfs,
I feel more alone than ever.</i>

452
00:42:13,070 --> 00:42:18,070
<i>/know you, of all people,
will understand.</i>

453
00:42:50,482 --> 00:42:55,319
Hello, Harry Potter.

454
00:42:55,320 --> 00:43:00,320
- Your feet. Aren't they cold?
- Bit.

455
00:43:00,868 --> 00:43:05,455
Unfortunately, all my shoes
have mysteriously disappeared.

456
00:43:05,456 --> 00:43:10,456
I suspect Nargles are behind it.

457
00:43:14,882 --> 00:43:19,177
- What are they?
- They're called Thestrals.

458
00:43:19,178 --> 00:43:24,178
They're quite gentle, really, but people
avoid them because they're a bit...

459
00:43:27,186 --> 00:43:31,939
Different.

460
00:43:31,940 --> 00:43:34,484
But why can't the others see them?

461
00:43:34,485 --> 00:43:39,485
They can only be seen
by people who've seen death.

462
00:43:40,115 --> 00:43:42,909
So you've known someone
Who's died, then?

463
00:43:42,910 --> 00:43:45,078
My mum.

464
00:43:45,079 --> 00:43:50,079
She was quite an extraordinary witch,
but she did like to experiment...

465
00:43:50,167 --> 00:43:53,628
and one day,
one of her spells went badly wrong.

466
00:43:53,629 --> 00:43:56,589
- I was 9.
- I'm sorry.

467
00:43:56,590 --> 00:43:58,966
Yes, it was rather horrible.

468
00:43:58,967 --> 00:44:03,967
I do feel very sad about it sometimes,
but I've got Dad.

469
00:44:06,517 --> 00:44:11,517
We both believe you, by the way.

470
00:44:12,231 --> 00:44:15,399
That He-Who-Must-Not-Be-Named
is back, and you fought him...

471
00:44:15,400 --> 00:44:18,694
and the Ministry and the Prophet
are conspiring against you.

472
00:44:18,695 --> 00:44:23,199
Thanks. It seems you're about
the only ones that do.

473
00:44:23,200 --> 00:44:26,911
I don't think that's true.

474
00:44:26,912 --> 00:44:30,206
But I suppose
that's how he wants you to feel.

475
00:44:30,207 --> 00:44:32,625
What do you mean?

476
