01:05:46,273 --> 01:05:51,273
I've never been able
to stun anything before.

720
01:05:58,327 --> 01:06:03,327
Mistletoe.

721
01:06:03,499 --> 01:06:06,501
Probably full of Nargles, though.

722
01:06:06,502 --> 01:06:08,878
What are Nargles?

723
01:06:08,879 --> 01:06:09,379
Noidea.

724
01:06:32,653 --> 01:06:35,613
<i>Well, how was it?</i>

725
01:06:35,614 --> 01:06:37,782
Wet.

726
01:06:37,783 --> 01:06:39,909
I mean, she was sort of Crying.

727
01:06:39,910 --> 01:06:42,036
That bad at it, are you?

728
01:06:42,037 --> 01:06:47,037
I'm sure Ham/s kissing
was more than satisfactory.

729
01:06:47,626 --> 01:06:49,961
Cho spends half her time
Crying these days.

730
01:06:49,962 --> 01:06:53,715
You'd think a bit of snogging
would Cheer her up.

731
01:06:53,716 --> 01:06:58,716
Don't you understand
how she must be feeling?

732
01:07:00,973 --> 01:07:04,601
Well, obviously
she's feeling sad about Cedric...

733
01:07:04,602 --> 01:07:07,854
and Confused about liking Harry
and guilty about kissing him...

734
01:07:07,855 --> 01:07:11,232
conflicted because Umbridge might
sack her mum from the Ministry...

735
01:07:11,233 --> 01:07:16,233
and frightened of failing her OWLs
because she's worrying about everything.

736
01:07:16,906 --> 01:07:20,658
One person couldn't feel all that.
They'd explode.

737
01:07:20,659 --> 01:07:25,659
Just because you've got
the emotional range of a teaspoon...

738
01:07:40,387 --> 01:07:40,887
<i>Harry.</i>

739
01:07:50,147 --> 01:07:53,900
<i>Voldemort may be after something.</i>

740
01:07:53,901 --> 01:07:57,737
<i>Something he didn't have last time.</i>

741
01:07:57,738 --> 01:08:00,615
<i>Harry.</i>

742
01:08:00,616 --> 01:08:01,116
<i>Harry.</i>

743
01:08:32,982 --> 01:08:36,568
In the dream,
were you standing next to the victim...

744
01:08:36,569 --> 01:08:38,528
or looking down at the scene?

745
01:08:38,529 --> 01:08:42,031
Neither. It was like I...

746
01:08:42,032 --> 01:08:44,325
Will you please just tell me
what's happening?

747
01:08:44,326 --> 01:08:46,828
Everard, Arthur's on guard duty
tonight.

748
01:08:46,829 --> 01:08:49,414
Make sure he's found
by the right people.

749
01:08:49,415 --> 01:08:51,165
- Sir.
- Phineas.

750
01:08:51,166 --> 01:08:53,626
You must go to your portrait
at Grimmauld Place.

751
01:08:53,627 --> 01:08:56,421
Tell them that Arthur Weasley
is gravely injured...

752
01:08:56,422 --> 01:09:00,758
and his children will be arriving there
soon by Portkey.

753
01:09:00,759 --> 01:09:04,012
They've got him, Albus. It was close,
but they think he'll make it.

754
01:09:04,013 --> 01:09:06,681
What's more,
the Dark Lord failed to acquire it.

755
01:09:06,682 --> 01:09:08,766
Oh, thank goodness. Next we need to...

756
01:09:08,767 --> 01:09:13,767
Look at me!

757
01:09:16,483 --> 01:09:21,483
What's happening to me?

758
01:09:26,577 --> 01:09:28,620
You wished to see me, headmaster?

759
01:09:28,621 --> 01:09:33,621
Oh, Severus. I'm afraid we can't wait.
Not even till the morning.

760
01:09:33,917 --> 01:09:38,917
Otherwise, we'll all be vulnerable.

761
01:09:41,592 --> 01:09:43,384
It appears there's a connection...

762
01:09:43,385 --> 01:09:45,887
between the Dark Lord's mind
and your own.

763
01:09:45,888 --> 01:09:50,391
Whether he is, as yet, aware of this
connection is, for the moment, unclear.

764
01:09:50,392 --> 01:09:53,603
Pray he remains ignorant.

765
01:09:53,604 --> 01:09:57,357
You mean, if he knows about it, then...

766
01:09:57,358 --> 01:10:01,903
- ...he'll be able to read my mind?
- Read it, control it...

767
01:10:01,904 --> 01:10:03,946
unhinge it.

768
01:10:03,947 --> 01:10:07,492
In the past, it was often
the Dark Lord's pleasure...

769
01:10:07,493 --> 01:10:09,911
to invade the minds of his victims...

770
01:10:09,912 --> 01:10:14,624
creating visions designed
to torture them into madness.

771
01:10:14,625 --> 01:10:19,587
Only after extracting the last exquisite
ounce of agony...

772
01:10:19,588 --> 01:10:24,050
only when he had them literally
begging for death, would he finally...

773
01:10:24,051 --> 01:10:26,260
kill them.

774
01:10:26,261 --> 01:10:28,846
Used properly,
the power of Occlumency...

775
01:10:28,847 --> 01:10:32,517
will help shield you
from access or influence.

776
01:10:32,518 --> 01:10:37,518
In these lessons, I will attempt
to penetrate your mind.

777
01:10:37,856 --> 01:10:41,234
You will attempt to resist.

778
01:10:41,235 --> 01:10:45,446
Prepare yourself.

779
01:10:45,447 --> 01:10:50,447
<i>Legilimens.</i>

780
01:10:54,790 --> 01:10:59,790
Concentrate, Potter. Focus.

781
01:11:24,278 --> 01:11:27,113
<i>Ho, ho, ho. Merry Christmas.</i>

782
01:11:27,114 --> 01:11:29,949
Here we go.

783
01:11:29,950 --> 01:11:34,950
Daddy's back.

784
01:11:35,289 --> 01:11:39,083
Sit down, everybody, sit down.
That's it. Now, presents.

785
01:11:39,084 --> 01:11:44,084
- And a nice big box for Ron.
- Big box for you. And...

786
01:11:46,258 --> 01:11:48,634
Fred and George. Come on, open up.

787
01:11:48,635 --> 01:11:51,095
- I want to see your faces.
- Yes.

788
01:11:51,096 --> 01:11:53,681
- Try it on.
- Thanks, Mum. It's perfect.

789
01:11:53,682 --> 01:11:58,144
- Just what he wanted, actually.
- Yeah. Right. Thanks, Mum.

790
01:11:58,145 --> 01:12:01,189
Come on, then, everybody.
Let's clear this away.

791
01:12:01,190 --> 01:12:03,357
Oh, Harry, Harry.

792
01:12:03,358 --> 01:12:06,277
There you are.

793
01:12:06,278 --> 01:12:08,696
- Happy Christmas.
- Thank you.

794
01:12:08,697 --> 01:12:10,698
- Lovely to have you with us.
- Thank you.

795
01:12:10,699 --> 01:12:12,867
Now, Daddy. Pass that to Daddy.

796
01:12:12,868 --> 01:12:14,744
- Thank you.
- Has everybody got?

797
01:12:14,745 --> 01:12:16,287
Fred? George?

798
01:12:16,288 --> 01:12:18,998
- Hermione.
- A Christmas toast.

799
01:12:18,999 --> 01:12:21,876
To Mr. Harry Potter...

800
01:12:21,877 --> 01:12:26,877
without whom I would not be here.

801
01:12:28,300 --> 01:12:30,802
,Harry-, Harry-

802
01:12:30,803 --> 01:12:33,054
Harry.

803
01:12:33,055 --> 01:12:35,807
That is delicious.
I shall be needing some more of that.

804
01:12:35,808 --> 01:12:39,101
Daddy, don't forget last Christmas.

805
01:12:39,102 --> 01:12:43,314
I can't understand
why you don't want to wear it, Ronald.

806
01:12:43,315 --> 01:12:45,316
I look like a bloody idiot, that's why.

807
01:12:45,317 --> 01:12:47,360
No more than usual, Ron.

808
01:12:47,361 --> 01:12:52,361
I don't know why...

809
01:12:55,202 --> 01:12:59,956
Nasty brat, standing there
as bold as brass.

810
01:12:59,957 --> 01:13:04,877
Harry Potter,
the boy who stopped the Dark Lord.

811
01:13:04,878 --> 01:13:08,297
Friend of Mudbloods
and blood-traitors alike.

812
01:13:08,298 --> 01:13:11,092
- If my poor mistress only knew...
- Kreacher!

813
01:13:11,093 --> 01:13:14,095
That's enough of your bile.
Away with you!

814
01:13:14,096 --> 01:13:16,264
Of course, master.

815
01:13:16,265 --> 01:13:21,265
Kreacher lives to serve
the noble house of Black.

816
01:13:23,272 --> 01:13:25,731
Sorry about that.

817
01:13:25,732 --> 01:13:29,735
He never was very pleasant,
even when I was a boy.

818
01:13:29,736 --> 01:13:32,655
Not to me, anyway.

819
01:13:32,656 --> 01:13:34,782
What, you grew up here?

820
01:13:34,783 --> 01:13:37,368
This is my parents' house.

821
01:13:37,369 --> 01:13:42,331
I offered it to Dumbledore
as headquarters for the Order.

822
01:13:42,332 --> 01:13:47,003
About the only useful thing
I've been able to do.

823
01:13:47,004 --> 01:13:50,298
This is the Black family tree.

824
01:13:50,299 --> 01:13:52,592
My deranged cousin.

825
01:13:52,593 --> 01:13:55,469
I hated the lot of them.

826
01:13:55,470 --> 01:14:00,470
My parents with their pure-blood mania.

827
01:14:03,395 --> 01:14:08,395
My mother did that after I ran away.

828
01:14:09,526 --> 01:14:12,653
Charming woman.

829
01:14:12,654 --> 01:14:15,156
I was 16.

830
01:14:15,157 --> 01:14:18,659
Where did you go?

831
01:14:18,660 --> 01:14:21,412
Round your dad's.

832
01:14:21,413 --> 01:14:24,832
I was always welcome at the Potters'.

833
01:14:24,833 --> 01:14:28,210
I see him so much in you, Harry.

834
01:14:28,211 --> 01:14:31,339
You are so very much alike.

835
01:14:31,340 --> 01:14:34,383
I'm not so sure.

836
01:14:34,384 --> 01:14:38,679
Sirius, when I was...

837
01:14:38,680 --> 01:14:43,680
When I saw Mr. Weasley attacked,
I wasn't just watching.

838
01:14:44,353 --> 01:14:46,687
I was the Snake.

839
01:14:46,688 --> 01:14:49,815
And afterwards,
in Dumbledore's office...

840
01:14:49,816 --> 01:14:54,816
there was a moment
when I wanted to...

841
01:14:59,159 --> 01:15:02,703
This connection
between me and Voldemort.

842
01:15:02,704 --> 01:15:07,625
What if the reason for it
is that I am becoming more like him?

843
01:15:07,626 --> 01:15:12,626
I just feel so angry all the time.

844
01:15:12,714 --> 01:15:17,426
And what if, after everything
that I've been through...

845
01:15:17,427 --> 01:15:22,427
something's gone wrong inside me?
What if I'm becoming bad?

846
01:15:23,642 --> 01:15:28,062
I want you to listen to me
very carefully, Harry.

847
01:15:28,063 --> 01:15:31,899
You're not a bad person.

848
01:15:31,900 --> 01:15:36,862
You're a very good person
who bad things have happened to.

849
01:15:36,863 --> 01:15:40,074
You understand?

850
01:15:40,075 --> 01:15:45,075
Besides, the world isn't split
into good people and Death Eaters.

851
01:15:45,288 --> 01:15:50,288
We've all got both light and dark
inside of us.

852
01:15:50,502 --> 01:15:55,502
What matters
is the part we choose to act on.

853
01:15:55,716 --> 01:16:00,716
That's who we really are.

854
01:16:01,763 --> 01:16:05,266
Harry, time to go.

855
01:16:05,267 --> 01:16:09,729
When all this is over,
we'll be a proper family.

856
01:16:09,730 --> 01:16:12,440
You'll see.

857
01:16:12,441 --> 01:16:12,985
Come on.

858
01:16:51,271 --> 01:16:52,605
Really?

859
01:16:52,606 --> 01:16:55,399
Harry. Harry.

860
01:16:55,400 --> 01:17:00,279
Hagrid's back.

861
01:17:00,280 --> 01:17:05,280
I'm sorry.

862
01:17:16,338 --> 01:17:19,799
I will say this one last time.

863
01:17:19,800 --> 01:17:22,343
I'm ordering you to tell me
where you've been.

864
01:17:22,344 --> 01:17:25,679
I told you. I've been away
for me health.

865
01:17:25,680 --> 01:17:30,017
- Your health?
- Yeah. Bit of fresh air, you know.

866
01:17:30,018 --> 01:17:35,018
Oh, yes. As gamekeeper,
fresh air must be difficult to come by.

867
01:17:36,900 --> 01:17:39,568
If I were you,
I shouldn't get too used to being back.

868
01:17:39,569 --> 01:17:44,569
In fact, I mightn't bother
unpacking at all.

869
01:18:01,800 --> 01:18:05,803
This is top-secret, right?

870
01:18:05,804 --> 01:18:08,347
Dumbledore sent me
to parley with the giants.

871
01:18:08,348 --> 01:18:11,058
Giants?

872
01:18:11,059 --> 01:18:12,268
You found them?

873
01:18:12,269 --> 01:18:17,022
Well, they're not that hard to find, to be
perfectly honest. They're so big, see?

874
01:18:17,023 --> 01:18:20,234
I tried to convince them
to join the cause.

875
01:18:20,235 --> 01:18:23,612
But I wasn't the only one
that was trying to win them over.

876
01:18:23,613 --> 01:18:25,990
- Death Eaters?
- Yes.

877
01:18:25,991 --> 01:18:29,827
Trying to persuade them
to join You-Know-Who.

878
01:18:29,828 --> 01:18:32,371
- Did they?
- I gave them Dumbledore's message.

879
01:18:32,372 --> 01:18:37,372
Suppose some of them remember
he was friendly to them. I Suppose.

880
01:18:40,088 --> 01:18:42,089
And they did this to you?

881
01:18:42,090 --> 01:18:44,341
Not exactly, no.

882
01:18:44,342 --> 01:18:49,342
Oh, go on, you have it, then,
you dozy dog.

883
01:19:02,235 --> 01:19:04,778
It's changing out there.

884
01:19:04,779 --> 01:19:07,823
Just like last time.

885
01:19:07,824 --> 01:19:10,201
There's a storm coming, Harry.

886
01:19:10,202 --> 01:19:15,202
We'd all best be ready when she does.

887
01:19:50,283 --> 01:19:53,494
<i>We have confirmed
that 10 high-security prisoners...</i>

888
01:19:53,495 --> 01:19:56,497
in <i>the early hours of yesterday evening
did escape.</i>

889
01:19:56,498 --> 01:20:00,334
<i>And of course, the Mugg/e prime minister
has been alerted to the danger.</i>

890
01:20:00,335 --> 01:20:03,254
<i>We strongly suspect...</i>

891
01:20:03,255 --> 01:20:05,422
that the breakout was engineered...

892
01:20:05,423 --> 01:20:09,802
by a man with personal experience
in escaping from Azkaban...

893
01:20:09,803 --> 01:20:14,803
notorious mass murderer Sirius Black...

894
01:20:15,475 --> 01:20:20,475
<i>cousin of escapee
Bellatrix Lestrange.</i>

895
01:20:30,156 --> 01:20:32,616
Dumbledore warned Fudge
this could happen.

896
01:20:32,617 --> 01:20:35,953
He's gonna get us all killed
just because he can't face the truth.

897
01:20:35,954 --> 01:20:36,454
Harry.

898
01:20:40,792 --> 01:20:43,377
I wanted to apologize.

899
01:20:43,378 --> 01:20:47,715
Now even me mum says the Prophet's
version of things don't add up.

900
01:20:47,716 --> 01:20:52,716
So, what I'm really trying to say
is that I believe you.

901
01:21:00,562 --> 01:21:01,062
Nevme?

902
01:21:14,743 --> 01:21:17,077
Fourteen years ago...

903
01:21:17,078 --> 01:21:21,498
a Death Eater
named Bellatrix Lestrange...

904
01:21:21,499 --> 01:21:25,252
used a Cruciatus Curse
on my parents.

905
01:21:25,253 --> 01:21:29,423
She tortured them for information...

906
01:21:29,424 --> 01:21:33,260
but they never gave in.

907
01:21:33,261 --> 01:21:36,722
I'm quite proud to be their son.

908
01:21:36,723 --> 01:21:41,723
But I'm not sure I'm ready
for everyone to know just yet.

909
01:21:46,524 --> 01:21:51,524
We're gonna make them proud, Neville.
That's a promise.

910
01:21:54,908 --> 01:21:58,786
Make it a powerful memory,
the happiest you can remember.

911
01:21:58,787 --> 01:22:02,373
Allow it to fill you up.
Keep trying, Seamus.

912
01:22:02,374 --> 01:22:05,125
George, your turn now.

913
01:22:05,126 --> 01:22:08,379
<i>Expecto Patronum.</i>

914
01:22:08,380 --> 01:22:11,965
A full-bodied Patronus
is the most difficult to produce...

915
01:22:11,966 --> 01:22:15,969
but shield forms can also be equally
useful against a variety of opponents.

916
01:22:15,970 --> 01:22:17,930
Wow, that was really good.

917
01:22:17,931 --> 01:22:19,640
Fantastic, Ginny.

918
01:22:19,641 --> 01:22:23,852
Just remember, your Patronus can only protect
you for as long as you stay focused.

919
01:22:23,853 --> 01:22:28,853
So focus, Luna.

920
01:22:29,859 --> 01:22:31,735
Think of the happiest thing you can.

921
01:22:31,736 --> 01:22:33,862
<i>Expecto Patronum.</i>

922
01:22:33,863 --> 01:22:36,907
- I'm trying.
- I know. It's good.

923
01:22:36,908 --> 01:22:41,908
This is really advanced stuff, guys.
You're doing so well.

924
01:22:41,913 --> 01:22:46,913
<i>Expecto Patronum.</i>

925
01:23:26,166 --> 01:23:30,043
I'll make short work of this.

926
01:23:30,044 --> 01:23:35,044
<i>Bombarda Maxima.</i>

927
01:23:50,315 --> 01:23:52,107
Get them.

928
01:23:52,108 --> 01:23:53,734
Been watching them for weeks.

929
01:23:53,735 --> 01:23:56,111
And see, "Dumbledore's Army"...

930
01:23:56,112 --> 01:24:01,112
proof of what I've been telling you
right from the beginning, Cornelius.

931
01:24:01,159 --> 01:24:03,410
All your fear-mongering
about You-Know-Who...

932
01:24:03,411 --> 01:24:05,120
never fooled us for a minute.

933
01:24:05,121 --> 01:24:07,372
We saw your lies for what they were:

934
01:24:07,373 --> 01:24:11,335
A smokescreen for your bid
to seize control of the Ministry.

935
01:24:11,336 --> 01:24:12,544
Naturally.

936
01:24:12,545 --> 01:24:15,255
No, professor.
He had nothing to do with it. It was me.

937
01:24:15,256 --> 01:24:19,092
Most noble of you, Harry, to shield me,
but as has been pointed out...

938
01:24:19,093 --> 01:24:24,093
the parchment clearly says
"Dumbledore's Army," not "Potter's."

939
01:24:24,098 --> 01:24:26,892
I instructed Harry
to form this organization.

940
01:24:26,893 --> 01:24:30,521
And I, and I alone,
am responsible for its activities.

941
01:24:30,522 --> 01:24:32,523
Dispatch an owl to the <i>Daily</i> Prophet.

942
01:24:32,524 --> 01:24:35,234
If we hurry, we should still make
the morning edition.

943
01:24:35,235 --> 01:24:40,197
Dawlish, Shacklebolt,
you will escort Dumbledore...

944
01:24:40,198 --> 01:24:42,866
to Azkaban...

945
01:24:42,867 --> 01:24:47,867
to await trial
for conspiracy and sedition.

946
01:24:48,206 --> 01:24:52,292
I thought we might hit this little snag.

947
01:24:52,293 --> 01:24:56,296
You seem to be laboring
under the delusion that I'm going to...

948
01:24:56,297 --> 01:24:57,923
What was the phrase?

949
01:24:57,924 --> 01:24:59,675
Come quietly.

950
01:24:59,676 --> 01:25:01,802
Well, I can tell you this:

951
01:25:01,803 --> 01:25:04,304
I have no intention
of going to Azkaban.

952
01:25:04,305 --> 01:25:06,056
Enough of this.

953
01:25:06,057 --> 01:25:06,669
Take him.

954
01:25:19,988 --> 01:25:24,533
Well, you may not like him, minister...

955
01:25:24,534 --> 01:25:27,202
but you can't deny...

956
01:25:27,203 --> 01:25:32,203
Dumbledore has got style.

957
01:25:54,147 --> 01:25:58,859
<i>Boys and girls are not permitted
to be within eight inches of each other.</i>

958
01:25:58,860 --> 01:26:02,446
<i>Those wishing to join
the Inquisitorial Squad for extra credit...</i>

959
01:26:02,447 --> 01:26:07,447
<i>Students will be submitted to question/bg
about suspected illicit activities.</i>

960
01:26:07,660 --> 01:26:12,660
<i>Any student in noncompliance
will be expel/ed.</i>

961
01:27:23,152 --> 01:27:23,652
Harry.

962
01:27:31,703 --> 01:27:35,288
You did everything you could.
No one could win against that old hag.

963
01:27:35,289 --> 01:27:38,542
Even Dumbledore
didn't see this coming.

964
01:27:38,543 --> 01:27:40,877
Harry, if it's anyone's fault, it's ours.

965
01:27:40,878 --> 01:27:43,130
Yeah, we talked you into it.

966
01:27:43,131 --> 01:27:45,674
Yeah, but I agreed.

967
01:27:45,675 --> 01:27:50,675
I tried so hard to help,
and all it's done is make things Worse.

968
01:27:51,848 --> 01:27:55,350
Anyway, that doesn't matter anymore.

969
01:27:55,351 --> 01:27:59,730
Because I don't want to play anymore.
All it does is make you care too much.

970
01:27:59,731 --> 01:28:02,566
And the more you care,
the more you have to lose.

971
01:28:02,567 --> 01:28:07,567
- So maybe it's just better to...
- To what?

972
01:28:07,989 --> 01:28:12,989
To go it alone.

973
01:28:16,247 --> 01:28:16,747
Hagñd.

974
01:28:21,669 --> 01:28:24,254
Any idea where he's taking us?

975
01:28:24,255 --> 01:28:29,255
Hagrid, why can't you just tell us?

976
01:28:35,641 --> 01:28:38,477
I've never seen the centaurs so riled.

977
01:28:38,478 --> 01:28:41,980
And they're dangerous
at the best of times.

978
01:28:41,981 --> 01:28:44,483
The Ministry restricts
their territory much more...

979
01:28:44,484 --> 01:28:46,860
they'll have a full uprising
on their hands.

980
01:28:46,861 --> 01:28:48,695
Hagrid, what's going on?

981
01:28:48,696 --> 01:28:51,072
I'm sorry to be so mysterious, you three.

982
01:28:51,073 --> 01:28:56,073
I wouldn't be bothering you at all with it,
but with Dumbledore gone...

983
01:28:56,704 --> 01:29:00,040
I'll likely be getting the sack
any day now.

984
01:29:00,041 --> 01:29:05,041
And I just couldn't leave
without telling someone about him.

985
01:29:07,715 --> 01:29:08,215
GraWPY-

986
01:29:11,761 --> 01:29:16,761
Down here, you great buffoon.

987
01:29:20,228 --> 01:29:22,687
GraWPY-

988
01:29:22,688 --> 01:29:27,688
Brought you some company.

989
01:29:36,744 --> 01:29:39,162
I couldn't just leave him, because...

990
01:29:39,163 --> 01:29:41,081
Because he's my brother.

991
01:29:41,082 --> 01:29:42,374
Blimey.

992
01:29:42,375 --> 01:29:44,584
Well, half brother, really.

993
01:29:44,585 --> 01:29:49,585
He's completely harmless, just like I said.
Little high-spirited, is all.

994
01:29:51,968 --> 01:29:54,469
- Grawpy, that is not polite.
- Hagrid, do something.

995
01:29:54,470 --> 01:29:57,055
We talked about this.
You do not grab, do you?

996
01:29:57,056 --> 01:29:59,474
That's your new friend, Hermione.

997
01:29:59,475 --> 01:29:59,975
GraWPY-

998
01:30:05,106 --> 01:30:08,316
Grawp.

999
01:30:08,317 --> 01:30:13,317
Put me down.

1000
01:30:15,074 --> 01:30:15,574
Now.

1001
01:30:28,796 --> 01:30:31,172
You all right?

1002
01:30:31,173 --> 01:30:33,258
Fine.

1003
01:30:33,259 --> 01:30:35,719
Just needs a firm hand, is all.

1004
01:30:35,720 --> 01:30:40,640
I think you've got an admirer.

1005
01:30:40,641 --> 01:30:45,641
You just stay away from her, all right?

1006
01:31:12,924 --> 01:31:16,927
He gets his own food and all.

1007
01:31:16,928 --> 01:31:21,348
It's company he'll be needing
when I'm gone.

1008
01:31:21,349 --> 01:31:24,059
You will look after him, won't you?

1009
01:31:24,060 --> 01:31:29,060
I'm the only family he's got.

1010
01:31:40,368 --> 01:31:45,368
Feeling sentimental?

1011
01:31:45,498 --> 01:31:49,626
- That's private.
- Not to me.

1012
01:31:49,627 --> 01:31:54,627
And not to the Dark Lord,
if you don't improve.

1013
01:31:55,549 --> 01:31:58,885
Every memory he has access to
is a weapon he can use against you.

1014
01:31:58,886 --> 01:32:03,886
You won't last two seconds
if he invades your mind.

1015
01:32:04,225 --> 01:32:06,643
You're just like your father.

1016
01:32:06,644 --> 01:32:08,603
Lazy, arrogant.

1017
01:32:08,604 --> 01:32:11,022
- Don't say a word against my father.
- Weak.

1018
01:32:11,023 --> 01:32:13,817
- I'm not weak.
- Then prove it.

1019
01:32:13,818 --> 01:32:15,902
Control your emotions.

1020
01:32:15,903 --> 01:32:20,903
Discipline your mind.

1021
01:32:21,701 --> 01:32:26,701
<i>Legilimens.</i>

1022
01:32:30,084 --> 01:32:31,376
<i>Harry.</i>

1023
01:32:31,377 --> 01:32:33,753
Sirius.

1024
01:32:33,754 --> 01:32:35,422
<i>I may vomit.</i>

1025
01:32:35,423 --> 01:32:37,590
Stop it.

1026
01:32:37,591 --> 01:32:40,385
Is this what you call control?

1027
01:32:40,386 --> 01:32:43,596
We've been at it for hours.
If I could just rest.

1028
01:32:43,597 --> 01:32:48,597
The Dark Lord isn't resting.

1029
01:32:48,644 --> 01:32:50,729
You and Black, you're two of a kind.

1030
01:32:50,730 --> 01:32:54,858
Sentimental children forever whining
about how unfair your lives have been.

1031
01:32:54,859 --> 01:32:58,403
Well, it may have escaped your notice,
but life isn't fair.

1032
01:32:58,404 --> 01:33:02,532
Your blessed father knew that.
In fact, he frequently saw to it.

1033
01:33:02,533 --> 01:33:06,619
- My father was a great man.
- Your father was a swine.

1034
01:33:06,620 --> 01:33:11,620
<i>- Legi/imens.
- Protega.</i>

1035
01:33:13,669 --> 01:33:15,378
Come on, Moony, Padfoot.

1036
01:33:15,379 --> 01:33:17,630
<i>Snape. Expelliarmus.</i>

1037
01:33:17,631 --> 01:33:19,799
Nice one, James.

1038
01:33:19,800 --> 01:33:22,302
<i>- Dad.
- Impedimenta.</i>

1039
01:33:22,303 --> 01:33:24,471
<i>Snivel/us Greasy.
Snivel/us Greasy.</i>

1040
01:33:24,472 --> 01:33:27,307
Right. Who wants to see me
take off Snivelly's trousers?

1041
01:33:27,308 --> 01:33:29,726
<i>Snivel/us Greasy.
Snivel/us Greasy.</i>

1042
01:33:29,727 --> 01:33:32,896
<i>Enough.</i>

1043
01:33:32,897 --> 01:33:33,397
Enough.

1044
01:33:42,990 --> 01:33:45,784
Your lessons are at an end.

1045
01:33:47,078 --> 01:33:47,622
Get out.

1046
01:34:07,556 --> 01:34:09,891
- What's your name?
- Michael.

1047
01:34:09,892 --> 01:34:11,976
Your hand's gonna be fine, Michael.

1048
01:34:11,977 --> 01:34:15,188
Yeah. It's not as bad as it seems. See?

1049
01:34:15,189 --> 01:34:17,357
It's fading already.

1050
01:34:17,358 --> 01:34:22,358
You can hardly see ours anymore,
and the pain stops after a while.

1051
01:34:29,495 --> 01:34:32,372
As I told you once before, Mr. Potter...

1052
01:34:32,373 --> 01:34:37,373
naughty children
deserve to be punished.

1053
01:34:39,213 --> 01:34:40,713
You know, George...

1054
01:34:40,714 --> 01:34:44,551
I've always felt our futures lay outside
the world of academic achievement.

1055
01:34:44,552 --> 01:34:49,552
Fred, I've been thinking
exactly the same thing.

1056
01:36:01,086 --> 01:36:06,086
All right, professor!

1057
01:36:11,513 --> 01:36:16,513
Here you go.

1058
01:36:38,249 --> 01:36:43,249
Ready when you are.

1059
01:38:05,836 --> 01:38:09,255
I need that prophecy.

1060
01:38:09,256 --> 01:38:11,924
You'll have to kill me.

1061
01:38:11,925 --> 01:38:16,679
Oh, I will.
But first, you will fetch it for me.

1062
01:38:16,680 --> 01:38:17,180
<i>Crucio.</i>

1063
01:38:20,934 --> 01:38:21,434
<i>Crucio.</i>

1064
01:38:34,073 --> 01:38:35,698
Sirius.

1065
01:38:35,699 --> 01:38:36,908
Harry, are you sure?

1066
01:38:36,909 --> 01:38:39,494
I saw it. It's just like
with Mr. Weasley.

1067
01:38:39,495 --> 01:38:41,537
It's the door I've been dreaming about.

1068
01:38:41,538 --> 01:38:43,790
I couldn't remember
where I'd seen it before.

1069
01:38:43,791 --> 01:38:45,875
Sirius said Voldemort
was after something.

1070
01:38:45,876 --> 01:38:49,337
Something he didn't have the last time,
in the Department of Mysteries.

1071
01:38:49,338 --> 01:38:52,799
Harry, please, just listen.

1072
01:38:52,800 --> 01:38:56,094
What if Voldemort
meant for you to see this?

1073
01:38:56,095 --> 01:38:59,389
What if he's only hurting Sirius
because he's trying to get to you?

1074
01:38:59,390 --> 01:39:03,059
What if he is?
I'm supposed to just let him die?

1075
01:39:03,060 --> 01:39:08,060
Hermione,
he's the only family I've got left.

1076
01:39:09,108 --> 01:39:11,567
What do we do?

1077
01:39:11,568 --> 01:39:13,361
We'll have to use the Floo Network.

1078
01:39:13,362 --> 01:39:15,613
Umbridge has the chimneys
under surveillance.

1079
01:39:15,614 --> 01:39:19,992
Not all of them.

1080
01:39:19,993 --> 01:39:24,993
<i>Alohomora.</i>

1081
01:39:32,548 --> 01:39:34,424
Alert the Order if you can.

1082
01:39:34,425 --> 01:39:38,177
- Are you mental? We're going with you.
- It's too dangerous.

1083
01:39:38,178 --> 01:39:41,973
When are you going to get it
into your head? We're in this together.

1084
01:39:41,974 --> 01:39:45,351
That you are.

1085
01:39:45,352 --> 01:39:50,352
Caught this one
trying to help the Weasley girl.

1086
01:39:53,235 --> 01:39:55,528
You were going to Dumbledore,
weren't you?

1087
01:39:55,529 --> 01:39:57,697
- No.
- Liar.

1088
01:39:57,698 --> 01:40:00,700
- You sent for me, headmistress?
- Snape, yes.

1089
01:40:00,701 --> 01:40:04,620
The time has come for answers, whether
he wants to give them to me or not.

1090
01:40:04,621 --> 01:40:06,330
Have you brought the Veritaserum?

1091
01:40:06,331 --> 01:40:09,375
I'm afraid you've used up
all my stores interrogating students.

1092
01:40:09,376 --> 01:40:14,376
The last of it on Miss Chang.

1093
01:40:16,550 --> 01:40:18,217
Unless you wish to poison him...

1094
01:40:18,218 --> 01:40:23,218
And I assure you, I would have
the greatest sympathy if you did.

1095
01:40:23,265 --> 01:40:27,643
I cannot help you.

1096
01:40:27,644 --> 01:40:30,396
He's got Padfoot.

1097
01:40:30,397 --> 01:40:34,358
He's got Padfoot at the place
where it's hidden.

1098
01:40:34,359 --> 01:40:36,652
Padfoot? What is Padfoot?
Where what is hidden?

1099
01:40:36,653 --> 01:40:41,653
What is he talking about, Snape?

1100
01:40:44,870 --> 01:40:45,370
Noidea.

1101
01:40:51,376 --> 01:40:53,920
Very well.

1102
01:40:53,921 --> 01:40:56,631
You give me no choice, Potter.

1103
01:40:56,632 --> 01:40:59,759
As this is an issue
of Ministry security...

1104
01:40:59,760 --> 01:41:02,595
you leave me with...

1105
01:41:02,596 --> 01:41:05,348
no alternative.

1106
01:41:05,349 --> 01:41:07,725
The Cruciatus Curse
ought to loosen your tongue.

1107
01:41:07,726 --> 01:41:08,935
That's illegal.

1108
01:41:08,936 --> 01:41:13,936
What Cornelius doesn't know
won't hurt him.

1109
01:41:19,780 --> 01:41:22,782
Tell her, Harry!

1110
01:41:22,783 --> 01:41:25,451
Tell me what?

1111
01:41:25,452 --> 01:41:28,120
Well, if you won't tell her where it is...

1112
01:41:28,121 --> 01:41:31,499
I Will.

1113
01:41:31,500 --> 01:41:34,502
Where what is?

1114
01:41:34,503 --> 01:41:39,503
Dumbledore's secret weapon.

1115
01:41:41,802 --> 01:41:43,511
How much further?

1116
01:41:43,512 --> 01:41:47,181
Not far.

1117
01:41:47,182 --> 01:41:52,182
It had to be Somewhere
students wouldn't find it accidentally.

1118
01:41:55,232 --> 01:41:56,857
What are you doing?

1119
01:41:56,858 --> 01:42:01,858
Improvising.

1120
01:42:07,160 --> 01:42:10,079
Well?

1121
01:42:10,080 --> 01:42:15,080
Where is this weapon?

1122
01:42:17,129 --> 01:42:22,129
There isn't one, is there?

1123
01:42:22,175 --> 01:42:27,175
You were trying to trick me.

1124
01:42:28,515 --> 01:42:31,517
You know...

1125
01:42:31,518 --> 01:42:36,518
I really hate children.

1126
01:42:49,119 --> 01:42:54,119
You have no business here, Centaur.
This is a Ministry matter.

1127
01:42:56,209 --> 01:42:58,044
Lower your Weapons.

1128
01:42:58,045 --> 01:43:03,045
I warn you, under the law, as
creatures of near-human intelligence...

1129
01:43:03,759 --> 01:43:05,259
<i>Protego.</i>

1130
01:43:05,260 --> 01:43:07,053
How dare you?

1131
01:43:07,054 --> 01:43:09,305
Filthy half-breed.

1132
01:43:09,306 --> 01:43:14,306
<i>Incarcerous.</i>

1133
01:43:23,570 --> 01:43:26,322
Please. Please stop it. Please.

1134
01:43:26,323 --> 01:43:31,323
Now, enough. I will have order.

1135
01:43:39,836 --> 01:43:42,588
You filthy animal.

1136
01:43:42,589 --> 01:43:45,716
Do you know who I am?

1137
01:43:45,717 --> 01:43:48,719
Leave him alone. It's not his fault.

1138
01:43:48,720 --> 01:43:53,720
No, he doesn't understand.

1139
01:43:58,271 --> 01:44:01,899
Potter, do something.
Tell them I mean no harm.

1140
01:44:01,900 --> 01:44:03,984
I'm sorry, professor.

1141
01:44:03,985 --> 01:44:05,945
But I must not tell lies.

1142
01:44:05,946 --> 01:44:07,154
What are you doing?

1143
01:44:07,155 --> 01:44:11,450
I am Senior Undersecretary
Dolores Jane Umbridge.

1144
01:44:11,451 --> 01:44:16,288
Let me go!

1145
01:44:16,289 --> 01:44:18,290
Thank you, Grawp.

1146
01:44:18,291 --> 01:44:23,291
Hermione. Hermione, Sirius.

1147
01:44:30,053 --> 01:44:33,806
- How'd you get away?
- Puking Pastilles. It wasn't pretty.

1148
01:44:33,807 --> 01:44:36,100
Told them I was hungry,
wanted some sweets.

1149
01:44:36,101 --> 01:44:39,478
They told me to bugger off
and ate the lot themselves.

1150
01:44:39,479 --> 01:44:41,814
That was clever, Ron.

1151
01:44:41,815 --> 01:44:44,483
- Has been known to happen.
- It was brilliant.

1152
01:44:44,484 --> 01:44:47,653
So how are we getting to London?

1153
01:44:47,654 --> 01:44:52,032
Look, it's not that I don't appreciate
everything you've done, all of you...

1154
01:44:52,033 --> 01:44:54,910
but I've got you
into enough trouble as it is.

1155
01:44:54,911 --> 01:44:58,205
Dumbledore's Army's supposed to be
about doing something real.

1156
01:44:58,206 --> 01:45:02,209
Or was that all just words to you?

1157
01:45:02,210 --> 01:45:07,210
Maybe you don't have to do this
all by yourself, mate.

1158
01:45:10,343 --> 01:45:13,888
So how are we going to get to London?

1159
01:45:13,889 --> 01:45:18,889
We fly, of course.

1160
01:46:07,192 --> 01:46:12,192
<i>Department of Mysteries.</i>

1161
01:46:18,203 --> 01:46:23,203
This is it.

1162
01:47:12,883 --> 01:47:16,927
Ninety-two. Ninety-three.

1163
01:47:16,928 --> 01:47:19,555
Ninety-four.

1164
01:47:19,556 --> 01:47:24,556
Ninety-five.

1165
01:47:33,153 --> 01:47:38,153
- He should be here.
- Harm.

1166
01:47:38,617 --> 01:47:43,617
It's got your name on it.

1167
01:48:05,101 --> 01:48:10,101
<i>The one with the power
to Vanquish the Dark Lord approaches.</i>

1168
01:48:10,315 --> 01:48:12,900
<i>And the Dark Lord
shall mark him as his equal...</i>

1169
01:48:12,901 --> 01:48:17,901
<i>but he shall have power
the Dark Lord knows not.</i>

1170
01:48:21,368 --> 01:48:26,368
<i>For neither can live
while the other survives.</i>

1171
01:48:29,209 --> 01:48:29,709
Harry.

1172
01:48:40,804 --> 01:48:42,471
Where's Sirius?

1173
01:48:42,472 --> 01:48:47,472
You know, you really should learn
to tell the difference between dreams...

1174
01:48:50,480 --> 01:48:53,899
and reality.

1175
01:48:53,900 --> 01:48:58,900
You saw only what the Dark Lord
wanted you to see.

1176
01:48:59,572 --> 01:49:01,240
Now, hand me the prophecy.

1177
01:49:01,241 --> 01:49:06,078
If you do anything to us, I'll break it.

1178
01:49:06,079 --> 01:49:08,831
He knows how to play.

1179
01:49:08,832 --> 01:49:12,793
Itty, bitty baby.

1180
01:49:12,794 --> 01:49:14,586
Potter.

1181
01:49:14,587 --> 01:49:16,630
Bellatrix Lestrange.

1182
01:49:16,631 --> 01:49:19,758
Neville Longbottom, is it?
How's Mum and Dad?

1183
01:49:19,759 --> 01:49:24,430
Better, now they're
about to be avenged.

1184
01:49:24,431 --> 01:49:29,431
Now, let's everybody
just calm down...

1185
01:49:29,728 --> 01:49:31,395
shall we?

1186
01:49:31,396 --> 01:49:34,023
All we want is that prophecy.

1187
01:49:34,024 --> 01:49:36,400
Why did Voldemort
need me to come and get this?

1188
01:49:36,401 --> 01:49:39,570
You dare speak his name?

1189
01:49:39,571 --> 01:49:41,321
You filthy half-blood!

1190
01:49:41,322 --> 01:49:45,868
It's all right.
He's just a curious lad, aren't you?

1191
01:49:45,869 --> 01:49:50,869
Prophecies can only be retrieved
by those about whom they are made.

1192
01:49:51,499 --> 01:49:56,499
Which is lucky for you, really.

1193
01:49:58,006 --> 01:50:00,466
Haven't you always wondered...

1194
01:50:00,467 --> 01:50:05,467
the reason for the connection
between you and the Dark Lord?

1195
01:50:06,389 --> 01:50:09,058
Why he was unable to kill you...

1196
01:50:09,059 --> 01:50:12,978
when you were just an infant?

1197
01:50:12,979 --> 01:50:17,979
Don't you want to know
the secret of your scar?

1198
01:50:18,693 --> 01:50:23,693
All the answers are there, Potter,
in your hand.

1199
01:50:24,324 --> 01:50:26,867
All you have to do...

1200
01:50:26,868 --> 01:50:29,119
is give it to me.

1201
01:50:29,120 --> 01:50:34,120
Then I can show you everything.

1202
01:50:41,174 --> 01:50:43,550
I've waited 14 years.

1203
01:50:43,551 --> 01:50:46,178
I know.

1204
01:50:46,179 --> 01:50:49,264
I guess I can wait a little longer.
Now. Stupefy.

1205
01:50:49,265 --> 01:50:49,809
<i>Stupefy-</i>

1206
01:51:06,825 --> 01:51:11,825
<i>Le vicorpus.</i>

1207
01:51:14,374 --> 01:51:16,583
<i>Petrificus Tota/us.</i>

1208
01:51:16,584 --> 01:51:21,584
Well done, Neville.

1209
01:51:26,845 --> 01:51:30,139
<i>Stupefy-</i>

1210
01:51:30,140 --> 01:51:35,140
<i>_5tupefy. _5tupefy.</i>

1211
01:51:42,527 --> 01:51:43,071
<i>Stupefy-</i>

1212
01:51:51,953 --> 01:51:52,497
<i>Reducto.</i>

1213
01:52:10,263 --> 01:52:15,263
Get back to the door.

1214
01:52:47,675 --> 01:52:52,675
Department of Mysteries.
They got that bit right, didn't they?

1215
01:52:57,393 --> 01:52:59,853
The Voices.

1216
01:52:59,854 --> 01:53:03,565
Can you tell what they're saying?

1217
01:53:03,566 --> 01:53:06,485
There aren't any Voices, Harry.

1218
01:53:06,486 --> 01:53:08,403
Let's get out of here.

1219
01:53:08,404 --> 01:53:13,116
I hear them too.

1220
01:53:13,117 --> 01:53:18,117
Harry, it's just an empty archway.

1221
01:53:18,498 --> 01:53:20,666
Please, Harry.

1222
01:53:20,667 --> 01:53:25,667
Get behind me.

1223
01:54:09,090 --> 01:54:11,967
Did you actually believe...

1224
01:54:11,968 --> 01:54:16,968
or were you truly naive enough
to think...

1225
01:54:17,181 --> 01:54:22,181
that children stood a Chance
against us?

1226
01:54:25,815 --> 01:54:30,815
I'll make this simple for you, Potter.

1227
01:54:33,239 --> 01:54:36,742
Give me the prophecy now...

1228
01:54:36,743 --> 01:54:41,743
or watch your friends die.

1229
01:54:53,676 --> 01:54:58,676
Don't give it to him, Harry.

1230
01:55:21,371 --> 01:55:26,371
Get away from my godson.

1231
01:55:54,237 --> 01:55:57,155
Now, listen to me.
Take the others and get out of here.

1232
01:55:57,156 --> 01:55:59,157
What? No, I'm staying with you.

1233
01:55:59,158 --> 01:56:02,661
You've done beautifully.

1234
01:56:02,662 --> 01:56:04,454
Now, let me take it from here.

1235
01:56:04,455 --> 01:56:04,955
Black.

1236
01:56:32,650 --> 01:56:34,151
<i>Expe/liarmus!</i>

1237
01:56:34,152 --> 01:56:39,152
Nice one, James.

1238
01:56:42,702 --> 01:56:47,702
<i>Avada Kedavra.</i>

1239
01:57:04,390 --> 01:57:04,890
<i>No. No.</i>

1240
01:57:30,750 --> 01:57:34,294
I killed Sirius Black.

1241
01:57:34,295 --> 01:57:39,295
- You Coming to get me?
- Crucio.

1242
01:57:48,601 --> 01:57:51,937
<i>You've got to mean it, Harry.</i>

1243
01:57:51,938 --> 01:57:56,938
<i>She killed him. She deserves it.</i>

1244
01:57:59,529 --> 01:58:04,529
<i>You know the spe/I, Harry.</i>

1245
01:58:14,293 --> 01:58:14,793
Do it.

1246
01:58:23,594 --> 01:58:24,138
So weak.

1247
01:58:33,312 --> 01:58:36,690
It was foolish of you
to come here tonight, Tom.

1248
01:58:36,691 --> 01:58:38,608
The Aurors are on their way.

1249
01:58:38,609 --> 01:58:43,609
By which time I shall be gone,
and you...

1250
01:58:44,323 --> 01:58:49,323
shall be dead.

1251
02:01:00,751 --> 02:01:05,751
You've lost, old man.

1252
02:01:22,773 --> 02:01:23,273
Harry.

1253
02:01:27,945 --> 02:01:29,946
<i>So weak.</i>

1254
02:01:29,947 --> 02:01:34,947
<i>So vulnerable.</i>

1255
02:01:36,454 --> 02:01:39,998
Look at me.

1256
02:01:39,999 --> 02:01:44,419
Harry, it isn't how you are alike.

1257
02:01:44,420 --> 02:01:49,420
It's how you are not.

1258
02:01:51,844 --> 02:01:52,344
Harry?

1259
02:02:25,753 --> 02:02:27,837
You're the weak one...

1260
02:02:27,838 --> 02:02:32,838
and you'll never know
love or friendship.

1261
02:02:35,387 --> 02:02:40,387
And I feel sorry for you.

1262
02:03:01,330 --> 02:03:05,750
You're a fool, Harry Potter.

1263
02:03:05,751 --> 02:03:10,751
And you will lose everything.

1264
02:03:25,813 --> 02:03:30,813
He's back.

1265
02:04:35,215 --> 02:04:37,050
I know how you feel, Harry.

1266
02:04:37,051 --> 02:04:42,051
No, you don't.

1267
02:04:44,308 --> 02:04:45,850
It's my fault.

1268
02:04:45,851 --> 02:04:50,146
No, the fault is mine.

1269
02:04:50,147 --> 02:04:52,065
I knew it was only a matter of time...

1270
02:04:52,066 --> 02:04:55,944
before Voldemort made the connection
between you.

1271
02:04:55,945 --> 02:05:00,365
I thought by distancing myself from you,
as I have done all year...

1272
02:05:00,366 --> 02:05:05,366
he'd be less tempted, and therefore
you might be more protected.

1273
02:05:08,415 --> 02:05:12,377
The prophecy said:

1274
02:05:12,378 --> 02:05:17,378
"Neither one can live
while the other one survives."

1275
02:05:17,675 --> 02:05:22,675
it means one of us is gonna
have to kill the other, in the end.

1276
02:05:25,724 --> 02:05:27,767
Yes.

1277
02:05:27,768 --> 02:05:29,519
Why didn't you tell me?

1278
02:05:29,520 --> 02:05:33,272
For the same reason
you tried to save Sirius.

1279
02:05:33,273 --> 02:05:36,567
The same reason your friends saved you.

1280
02:05:36,568 --> 02:05:40,238
After all these years,
after all you've suffered...

1281
02:05:40,239 --> 02:05:44,617
I didn't want to cause you
any more pain.

1282
02:05:44,618 --> 02:05:49,618
I cared too much about you.

1283
02:06:11,603 --> 02:06:14,105
How come you're not at the feast?

1284
02:06:14,106 --> 02:06:18,818
Lost all my possessions. Apparently
people have been hiding them.

1285
02:06:18,819 --> 02:06:20,028
That's awful.

1286
02:06:20,029 --> 02:06:22,071
Oh, it's all good fun.

1287
02:06:22,072 --> 02:06:25,700
But as it's the last night,
I really do need them back.

1288
02:06:25,701 --> 02:06:30,701
Do you want any help finding them?

1289
02:06:30,956 --> 02:06:35,956
I'm sorry about your godfather, Harry.

1290
02:06:41,216 --> 02:06:43,468
Are you sure you don't want
any help looking?

1291
02:06:43,469 --> 02:06:45,303
That's all right.

1292
02:06:45,304 --> 02:06:47,638
Anyway, my mum always said...

1293
02:06:47,639 --> 02:06:52,639
the things we lose have a way
of coming back to us in the end.

1294
02:06:54,730 --> 02:06:59,484
If not always in the way we expect.

1295
02:06:59,485 --> 02:07:04,485
Think I'll just go have some pudding.

1296
02:07:37,856 --> 02:07:40,942
I've been thinking about something
Dumbledore said to me.

1297
02:07:40,943 --> 02:07:43,236
What's that?

1298
02:07:43,237 --> 02:07:46,197
That even though
we've got a fight ahead of us...

1299
02:07:46,198 --> 02:07:49,450
we've got one thing
that Voldemort doesn't have.

1300
02:07:49,451 --> 02:07:52,870
Yeah?

1301
02:07:52,871 --> 02:07:57,871
Something worth fighting for.

